codex
Local Chromium is blocked by the expected macOS service denial before page creation, so it cannot replay the pointer-event failure here; the two independent logs remain the authoritative red signal. Ranked hypotheses:

1. The loop calls `check()` on hidden switch inputs whose wrapping labels own the clickable surface; selecting the labels will pass.
2. The indexed checkbox collection becomes stale after React rerenders; resolving one current declaration at a time will pass.
3. The collection includes unrelated switches outside the declarations step; scoping to the visible declarations section will pass.
4. A transient overlay intercepts clicks; waiting would pass, though the repeated 30-second label interception makes this least likely.

I’ll inspect the existing declaration markup and tests to distinguish these without changing production code.
